 total area of this place is 86.82 square kilometers, with an average elevation of 24 meters above sea level. This plain region has its eastern and southern sides open, which direct slope down into the sea, while Mohiri or Kerandi hills border it from the north and west. It is very close to Andhra Pradesh, and therefore, one can find an amalgamation of Telugu-speaking and Odia or Oriya-speaking communities. This place is not just culturally rich, but it also has some amazing spots that are waiting to be explored. The list of top tourist places in Berhampur is as follows- 1. Gopalpur Beach Gopalpur Beach, situated on the Eastern Coast of India, is a beautiful beach in Odisha. It is a popular spot for Olive Ridley Turtle nesting. It is nestled among coconut and casuarina trees and makes for a great weekend getaway. This beach is also known as "Gopalpur-on-Sea" and has a tranquil and peaceful coast. Gopalpur beach festival is one of the major highlights of this beach. Apart from this, there are numerous aqua sports for you to enjoy. The lighthouse is a popular landmark on the beach. It offers spectacular views of Gopalpur, the Bay of Bengal, and the entire city. You can also see the red crabs strolling along the lonely beach coast. Gopalpur Beach offers ample opportunities for making your visit worthwhile. You can take a nice walk among the cashew trees or thrill yourself by participating in water sports. 2. Shopping in Berhampur This city is a great place to shop if you feel like going on a shopping spree, whether it be for clothes, handicrafts, or food. Berhampur is known for its silk sarees with a large diversity and glittering jewelry that sparkles to make the eyes twinkle. Tourists love the variety of delicious fruits found in the city, especially mangoes. Pickles, Papad, and Badis, are also popular. Local artisans spend many nights crafting artifacts that are exquisite. It is worth purchasing to preserve their culture. The city has a market area that hosts other 