ring waterfall that lies in thick forests. It is situated within Kamalapur, Gajapati district. It is about 90 kilometers away from Brahmapur. Tourists can access this hidden secret by hiring a private taxi or using automobiles. Khasada falls one of the tiny waterfalls that is located in dense forest. This is a natural waterfall that sits on a hilltop. It is necessary to walk a few miles to get there. Since it is surrounded by lush greenery all around, it is a great escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. If you're looking for peace and tranquillity, it will be ideal for your requirements. There are many visitors from across the world who visit the waterfall each year. Tourists should plan to spend at least an hour or more at this waterfall, enjoying the stunning views of the surrounding. It is possible to take a bath in the hot springs. It's a great place to picnic and enjoy time with your family and friends. Photographers will enjoy this location because it offers plenty of opportunities to see wildlife in the nearby forests as well as other stunning autumn views. Visitors can also visit Jiranaga Monastery from here, another hidden gem in Odisha. It is worth a visit if you happen to be in the vicinity. This waterfall is accessible every day of the week. There aren't any specific times for visiting this waterfall, but during the daytime, it is ideal. It may not be safe in the evenings and nights. How to reach Berhampur? Berhampur has good accessibility via roadways. It also has a railway station by the name of Brahmapur with station code BAM. However, this place lacks an airport. So, if you wish to travel by air, then you can take a flight to the nearest airport in Bhubaneshwar and then travel to Berhampur by road. The total distance between Bhubaneshwar airport and Berhampur is 172.1 kilometers and can be covered in less than 4 hours. The best time to visit this city is from October to June as the weather happens to be pleasant during this time. Also, durin